Sentencas: For an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC), the anode consists of a thick support layer with large pores and a thin functional layer with small pores.
Titulo: Phase Inversion Tape Casting and Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: In the present work, the anode of NiO and yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) comprising a porous support layer of similar to 700 mu m thick and a functional layer of similar to 60 mu m thick were formed in a single step using the phase inversion tape casting method.
Titulo: Phase Inversion Tape Casting and Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: For the as-prepared anode, the support layer contained large open pores which were aligned along the thickness direction.
Titulo: Phase Inversion Tape Casting and Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: A thin dense YSZ electrolyte layer with a thickness of 15 mu m was deposited onto the anode by dip-coating and co-sintering techniques.
Titulo: Phase Inversion Tape Casting and Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: A composite cathode of YSZ-La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta (LSM) with a weight ratio of 50:50 was screen-printed on the surface of the YSZ electrolyte layer.
Titulo: Phase Inversion Tape Casting and Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: The resulting fuel cell exhibited promising electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Phase Inversion Tape Casting and Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: A maximum power density of 891 mW/cm(2) was obtained at 800 degrees C using H-2-3% H2O as the fuel and ambient air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Phase Inversion Tape Casting and Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: The cell did not show any sign of concentration polarization even at high current densities, which should be attributed to the open straight pore structure and resultant fast gas-phase transport in the anode support.
Titulo: Phase Inversion Tape Casting and Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode
